<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1911/525245-625x325.jpg?2" alt="Image credit: Austin Distel on Unsplash." width="625" height="325">Image credit: Austin Distel on Unsplash.The podcast hit number one on the business section of iTunes, a couple of days after its release. A 'glocal' perspectiveSanei is a global speaker, best-selling author and trend specialist and Kruger is a keynote speaker, high-performance executive coach and author. They are good friends as well as colleagues and peers.The Expansive name was inspired by the work they do in helping people live lives that are constantly expanding in terms of possibility and purpose.<a href="https://iono.fm/e/757897">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>A new podcast is released every week and seven are currently available.Each podcast takes the form of a fairly informal discussion between Sanei and Kruger. They share the highs and lows of their personal and professional journeys and unpack how they find opportunity in challenge and high-performance in mediocrity.Since Sanei is in Dubai and Kruger is in Johannesburg, they bring a “glocal” perspective. The topics are decided on an ad-hoc basis.The average length of a podcast is 17 minutes.